{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"378feeb2-4b2c-4183-b197-4492ff4c350b","content":"\n\nIn your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Platform | Foreground flow | Background flow |\n|---|---|---|\n| All | `Created → Activated` | `Deactivated → Stopped` |\n| Resume | `Stopped → Resumed → Activated` | — |\n| Close | — | `Deactivated → Stopped → Destroying` |\n| iOS only | — | `Backgrounding` (before `Stopped`) |\n\n> `Backgrounding` is iOS-specific and is where you should save state. On Android/Windows, use `Stopped` instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2072fa20-412e-4e4a-9cb4-b7bb30e5d71f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging. This is a general knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to explore any codebase.","outputTokens":426},"id":"af40faba-fa9f-4258-9daf-121a3c68007b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:47:43.104Z","parentId":"20bace5e-3676-429c-be7a-8af002c2e329"}
